Summary of Material Information:

Announcement Type: Exploration Results Update

  • Key Findings:
  • Orion Project (Spain) shows potential for broad mineralization with multiple stratabound seams rich in rutile, zircon, hafnium, and rare earths (REE).

  • Full assay results pending (expected within weeks).

  • Next Steps:

  • Initial 15-hole drill program planned to confirm geological interpretation.

Material Information Summary (Prodigy Gold NL - ASX: PRX - 18 June 2025)

Metallurgical Testwork Results (Hyperion Gold Deposit)

  • Oxide & Transition Material:
  • 95%+ gold recovery using standard Gravity Gold/Carbon-in-Leach (GG/CIL) processing.
  • Fresh Material:
  • Refractory component identified (arsenopyrite association); initial recovery <70% with CIL alone.
  • Flotation + CIL improves recovery to 91.2% (5.8% gravity, 60.4% flotation, 25.0% cyanide leach of tails).
  • Next Steps:
  • Further testwork planned (heap leach potential, fine grinding, oxidative leaching).
  • Additional drilling (2025 field season) to expand resource, including govt.-funded diamond holes targeting high-grade Tethys lode (10m @ 15.9g/t Au).

Mineral Resource Context

  • Hyperion Resource (April 2025): 9.66Mt @ 1.4g/t Au (435koz) (cut-off: 0.5g/t Oxide/Transition, 0.6g/t Fresh).
  • Prodigy Gold Total Resources: 21.7Mt @ 1.4g/t Au (989koz).

Permitting & Development

  • Mineral Lease Application submitted (Dec 2024); approval expected in ~2 years.

Key Implications: Enhanced metallurgical recoveries support economic viability, particularly for Fresh material, with potential to upgrade resource confidence and project valuation. Drilling and permitting progress underscores near-term catalyst potential.

Top End Energy Limited (ASX: TEE) – Beetaloo Operational Update – Material Summary

  • Strategic Positioning: TEE holds EP 153 & EP 154 adjacent to Tamboran Resources’ EP 98 (7.1 Tcf 2C contingent resource) in the Beetaloo Sub-basin, near Amadeus Gas Pipeline.
  • Exploration Plans: Planned airborne gravity survey, seismic program, and drilling to define Beetaloo extension. Additional permit (EP 257) under application.
  • Near-Term Catalyst: Tamboran Resources reported record 30-day gas flow rate (7.2 MMcf/d), validating Beetaloo potential.

  • Hydrocarbon potential (analogue to Beetaloo) with core samples confirming TOC levels.
  • Hydrogen (up to 27%) & helium (0.9%) discoveries—additional revenue potential.
  • Proximity to Northern Gas Pipeline for east-coast market access.

No capital raising, financials, or concrete timelines—primarily strategic positioning update.

Material Information Summary (Exploration Results Announcement)

Key Highlights

  • New Mineralisation Discoveries:
  • Copperhead Corridor: Two major north-south structures (350m beyond known resource footprint) with significant intercepts:
    • 14m @ 0.81% Cu, 0.12 g/t Au, 749ppm Co (including 6m @ 1.37% Cu, 0.22 g/t Au, 1040ppm Co).
    • 11m @ 0.45% Cu, 0.08 g/t Au, 171ppm Co and 9m @ 0.66% Cu, 0.20 g/t Au, 460ppm Co.
  • Coppermine Creek: First drill intercept (12m @ 0.65% Cu, 0.16 g/t Au, 137ppm Co) confirms IOCG potential.
  • Paddock Lode South: 6m @ 0.63% Cu, 0.15 g/t Au, 75ppm Co expands Taipan Resource potential.

  • Orphan Shear: 9m @ 0.83% Cu, 0.07 g/t Au, 521ppm Co hints at deeper high-grade supergene zone.

  • Exploration Upside:

  • Shallow, high-grade intercepts suggest rapid near-surface resource expansion potential.

  • Follow-up drilling planned for Coppermine Creek, Copperhead, and Orphan Shear.

  • Next Steps:

  • Downhole EM surveys, 3D IP remodelling, and resource definition drilling programs.

Financial/Operational Impact

  • Potential to extend mine life and optimize mine plans at Cloncurry Copper Project (current resource: 12.69Mt @ 0.80% Cu, 0.19 g/t Au, 0.01% Co).

Conclusion

Material findings validate exploration strategy, with new zones likely to enhance resource inventory and project economics.
